{"title_page": "Cuarto, Ponce, Puerto Rico", "text_new": "{{short description|Barrio of Puerto Rico}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n<!-- Basic info  -------------- -->\n| official_name            = [[List of Barrios of Ponce|Barrio]] Cuarto\n| other_name               =\n| native_name              =\n| nickname                 =\n| settlement_type          =\n| motto                    =\n<!-- images and maps  --------- -->\n| image_skyline            = \n| imagesize                =\n| image_caption            =\n| image_flag               = \n| flag_size                =\n| image_seal               = \n| seal_size                =\n| image_blank_emblem       =\n| blank_emblem_type        =\n| blank_emblem_size        =\n| image_map                = Cuarto, Ponce, Puerto Rico.svg\n| mapsize                  = \n| map_caption              = Location of barrio Cuarto within the municipality of Ponce shown in red\n| image_map1               = \n| mapsize1                 = \n| map_caption1             =\n<!-- Location ---------------- -->\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Commonwealth (U.S. insular area)|Commonwealth]]\n| subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Puerto Rico}}\n| subdivision_type2 = [[List of municipalities in Puerto Rico|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name2 = {{flagicon image|Ponce2.gif}} [[Ponce, Puerto Rico|Ponce]]\n<!-- Politics --------------- -->\n| government_footnotes     =\n| government_type          =\n| leader_title             = \n| leader_name              = \n| leader_title1            = \n| leader_name1             =\n| leader_title2            =\n| leader_name2             =\n| established_title        = \n| established_date         = \n| established_title2       = \n| established_date2        =\n| established_title3       = \n| established_date3        =\n<!-- Area    ------------------- -->\n| area_magnitude           = 1 E7\n| unit_pref                = Imperial\n| area_footnotes           =\n| area_total_km2           = \n| area_land_km2            = \n| area_water_km2           = \n| area_total_sq_mi         = 0.17\n| area_land_sq_mi          = 0.16\n| area_water_sq_mi         = 0.00\n| area_water_percent       = \n| area_urban_km2           =\n| area_urban_sq_mi         =\n| area_metro_km2           =\n| area_metro_sq_mi         =\n| area_blank1_title        =\n| area_blank1_km2          =\n| area_blank1_sq_mi        =\n<!-- Population   --------------------- -->\n| population_as_of         = 2000\n| population_footnotes     = \n| population_note          = Source: 2000 Census\n| population_total         = 3,011\n| population_density_km2   = \n| population_density_sq_mi = 18819\n| population_metro         = \n| population_density_metro_km2     =\n| population_density_metro_sq_mi   =\n| population_urban                 =\n| population_density_urban_km2     =\n| population_density_urban_sq_mi   =\n| population_blank1_title          =\n| population_blank1                =\n| population_density_blank1_km2    =\n| population_density_blank1_sq_mi  =\n<!-- General information  ------------- -->\n| timezone                 =\n| utc_offset               =\n| timezone_DST             = \n| utc_offset_DST           = \n| latd =\n| longd =\n| elevation_footnotes      = \n| elevation_m              = \n| elevation_ft             = \n<!-- Area/postal codes & others ------ -->\n| postal_code_type         =\n| postal_code              =\n| area_code                = \n| blank_name               = \n| blank_info               = \n| blank1_name              = \n| blank1_info              = \n| website                  = \n| footnotes                =\n}}\n<!-- Infobox ends ! -->\n\n'''Cuarto''' (''Barrio Cuarto'') is one of the 31 [[barrio]]s of the municipality of [[Ponce, Puerto Rico]].  Together with [[Primero (Ponce)|Primero]], [[Segundo (Ponce)|Segundo]], [[Tercero (Ponce)|Tercero]], [[Quinto (Ponce)|Quinto]], and [[Sexto (Ponce)|Sexto]], Cuarto is one the municipality's [[Ponce, Puerto Rico#Barrios|six core urban barrios]]. It was created in 1878.<ref>[http://freepages.genealogy.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~poncepr/barrios.html ''Barrios de Ponce.''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930083458/http://freepages.genealogy.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~poncepr/barrios.html |date=30 September 2015 }} Antepasados Esclavos.(From: Pedro Tom\u00e1s de C\u00f3rdoba. Memorias geogr\u00e1ficas, hist\u00f3ricas, econ\u00f3micas y estad\u00edsticas de la Isla de Puerto Rico.) Retrieved 28 November 2014.</ref>\n\n==Location==\nCuarto is an urban barrio located in the southern section of the municipality, within the Ponce city limits, and southeast of the traditional center of the city, [[Plaza Las Delicias]].\n\n==Boundaries==\n[[File:Antiguo Casino de Ponce, in Ponce, Puerto Rico (IMG 2934).jpg|thumb|left|[[Old Ponce Casino|Casino de Ponce]], an important historic landmark, is located in Barrio Cuarto.]]\n\nIt is bounded on the North by Comercio/[[Francisco Parra Duper\u00f3n]] Street, on the South by [[Ram\u00f3n Power y Giralt|Ram\u00f3n Power]] Street, on the West by [[Eugenio Maria de Hostos]] Avenue and Marina Streets, and on the East by [[Rio Portugues]].<ref>[http://www.gis.otg.gobierno.pr/webcensus/ General Purpose Population Data, Census 2000. Unidad de Sistemas de Informaci\u00f3n Geogr\u00e1fica, \u00c1rea de Tecnolog\u00eda de Informaci\u00f3n Gubernamental, Oficina de Gerencia y Presupuesto. Gobierno de Puerto Rico.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100812171159/http://www.gis.otg.gobierno.pr/webcensus/ |date=August 12, 2010 }} Retrieved February 17, 2010.</ref>  In terms of barrio-to-barrio boundaries, Cuarto is bounded in the North by Barrio [[Tercero (Ponce)|Tercero]], in the South by [[Canas Urbano]], in the West by [[Primero (Ponce)|Primero]], and in the East by [[San Ant\u00f3n]].\n\n==Features and demographics==\nCuarto has {{convert|0.2|sqmi|m2|sigfig=2}} of land area and no water area.  In 2000, the population of Cuarto was 3,011. The population density in Cuarto was 18,303 persons per square mile.<ref>[http://www.citymelt.com/city/Puerto-Rico/Cuarto+Barrio-PR.html City Melt] Retrieved, February 17, 2010.</ref>\n\nThe communities of Belgica<ref>[http://www.letsgotoponce.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=161&Itemid=81 ''10,000 New Housing Units Expected for Ponce Historical District.'' Belgica sector to be renovated.] Retrieved April 15, 2010.</ref> and El Bosque are found in Barrio Cuarto as are several other smaller communities.\n\n==Landmarks==\nCuarto is home to [[Parque de la Abolicion]] on its southwestern edge. The [[NRHP]]-listed [[Casa Paoli]], [[Old Ponce Casino]], [[Ponce Massacre Museum]], and [[Iglesia de la Santisima Trinidad|Iglesia de la Sant\u00edsima Trinidad]] are all located in Barrio Cuarto. The Puerto Rico Islamic Center at Ponce (see side photo) is also located in Barrio Cuarto.\n[[File:IMG 3392 - Centro Islamico de Ponce, PR.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Puerto Rico Islamic Center at Ponce on Luna Street, Barrio Cuarto, a few blocks from downtown]]\n\n==Notable people from Barrio Cuarto==\n* [[Domingo Marrero Navarro]], educator, writer, and speaker from the Belgica sector of Barrio Cuarto.<ref>[http://www.metro.inter.edu/facultad/esthumanisticos/coleccion_domingo/Datos%20Biograficos%20Marrero.pdf ''Breves Datos Biogr\u00e1ficos del Rvdo. Prof. Domingo Marrero Navarro (1909\u20101960).''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100730034808/http://www.metro.inter.edu/facultad/esthumanisticos/coleccion_domingo/Datos%20Biograficos%20Marrero.pdf |date=30 July 2010 }} Interamerican University of Puerto Rico. Accessed 31 March 2018.</ref> \n* [[Ruth Fern\u00e1ndez]], internationally known contralto singer from the Belgica sector of Barrio Cuarto.<ref>[http://www.periodicolaperla.com/inmortalizaran-con-museo-a-la-negra-de-ponce/ ''Inmortalizar\u00e1n a La Negra de Ponce.''] Reinaldo Mill\u00e1n. La Perla del Sur. Ponce Puerto Rico. Year 30, Issue 1491. (27 June 2012) Page 12. Retrieved 4 July 2012. Weblink updated: 31 March 2018.</ref><ref>[http://www.prpop.org/biografias/r_bios/ruth_fernandez.shtml ''Biograf\u00edas: Ruth Fern\u00e1ndez.''] Fundaci\u00f3n Nacional para la Cultura Popular. 2011. Retrieved 7 December 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.enciclopediapr.org/ing/article.cfm?ref=06100235&highlight=%2Bruth+%2Bfernandez&page=4 ''Arts / History of Puerto Rican Music.''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120707074045/http://www.enciclopediapr.org/ing/article.cfm?ref=06100235&highlight=%2Bruth+%2Bfernandez&page=4 |date=2012-07-07 }} Encyclopedia Puerto Rico. Retrieved 7 December 2011.</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery class=\"center\" >\nFile:Restaurante '19 Barrios' de noche, C. Mayor y C. Aurora, Bo. Cuarto, Ponce, PR, mirando al sureste (DSC01426).jpg|Italian restaurant and bar on Calle Mayor and Calle Aurora\nFile:Museo de la Masacre de Ponce (IMG 2929).jpg|Human rights museum [[Museo de la Masacre de Ponce]] on Calle Marina\nFile:Concha Acustica de Ponce, Calle Marina and Calle Mayor, Barrio Cuarto, Ponce, Puerto Rico, looking south (DSC00373).jpg|Open-air amphitheater on Calle Marina and Calle Mayor\nFile:Holy Trinity Church in Barrio Cuarto in Ponce, PR, looking east (IMG 2980).jpg|The first (1873) Protestant church in Latin America, on Calle Marina  \nFile:Casa Paoli Ponce 330.jpg|Home of 'The king of tenors', [[Antonio Paoli]], on Calle Mayor\n</gallery>\n\n{{Coord|18.0072246|-66.6102100|region:US-PR_type:city(3011)_source:gnis|display=title|notes=<ref>{{Gnis|2415025|Cuarto Barrio}}</ref>}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of communities in Puerto Rico]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Portal|Puerto Rico}}\n\n{{Ponce, Puerto Rico}}\n\n[[Category:Barrios of Ponce, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:1878 establishments in Puerto Rico]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Barrio of Puerto Rico}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n<!-- Basic info  -------------- -->\n| official_name            = [[List of Barrios of Ponce|Barrio]] Cuarto\n| other_name               =\n| native_name              =\n| nickname                 =\n| settlement_type          =\n| motto                    =\n<!-- images and maps  --------- -->\n| image_skyline            = \n| imagesize                =\n| image_caption            =\n| image_flag               = \n| flag_size                =\n| image_seal               = \n| seal_size                =\n| image_blank_emblem       =\n| blank_emblem_type        =\n| blank_emblem_size        =\n| image_map                = Cuarto, Ponce, Puerto Rico.svg\n| mapsize                  = \n| map_caption              = Location of barrio Cuarto within the municipality of Ponce shown in red\n| image_map1               = \n| mapsize1                 = \n| map_caption1             =\n<!-- Location ---------------- -->\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Commonwealth (U.S. insular area)|Commonwealth]]\n| subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Puerto Rico}}\n| subdivision_type2 = [[List of municipalities in Puerto Rico|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name2 = {{flagicon image|Ponce2.gif}} [[Ponce, Puerto Rico|Ponce]]\n<!-- Politics --------------- -->\n| government_footnotes     =\n| government_type          =\n| leader_title             = \n| leader_name              = \n| leader_title1            = \n| leader_name1             =\n| leader_title2            =\n| leader_name2             =\n| established_title        = \n| established_date         = \n| established_title2       = \n| established_date2        =\n| established_title3       = \n| established_date3        =\n<!-- Area    ------------------- -->\n| area_magnitude           = 1 E7\n| unit_pref                = Imperial\n| area_footnotes           =\n| area_total_km2           = \n| area_land_km2            = \n| area_water_km2           = \n| ar